Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '293'. Name Andrias. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0049.24.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (26)
